  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "1 Kings 14:20",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 Kings 14:20",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Jeroboam reigned two and twenty years ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— So he lived till the second year of Asa, chap. 15. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "He slept with his fathers — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "He died as his fathers did, or perhaps the expression also implies, that he was buried with his ancestors. Their sepulchre, however, may appear too mean for a great king. It is probable that he died soon after his son: and we read, (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 13:20",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ",) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "The Lord struck him; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "probably with some sudden and sore disease, which soon cut him off. He left his crown to Nadab his son, who lost it, and his life too, and the lives of all his family, within ten years after. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "The triumphing of the wicked is short, and the joy of the hypocrite but for a moment, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Job 20:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
